{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":754,"text":"I'm going to talk today\nabout energy and climate."},{"time":5103,"text":"And that might seem a bit surprising,"},{"time":6905,"text":"because my full-time work\nat the foundation"},{"time":10078,"text":"is mostly about vaccines and seeds,"},{"time":12137,"text":"about the things that we need\nto invent and deliver"},{"time":15729,"text":"to help the poorest two billion\nlive better lives."},{"time":20481,"text":"But energy and climate\nare extremely important to these people;"},{"time":25000,"text":"in fact, more important\nthan to anyone else on the planet."},{"time":29793,"text":"The climate getting worse means\nthat many years, their crops won't grow:"},{"time":35528,"text":"there will be too much rain,\nnot enough rain;"},{"time":38583,"text":"things will change in ways their fragile\nenvironment simply can't support."},{"time":44544,"text":"And that leads to starvation, it leads\nto uncertainty, it leads to unrest."},{"time":48872,"text":"So, the climate changes\nwill be terrible for them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":52833,"text":"Also, the price of energy\nis very important to them."},{"time":56000,"text":"In fact, if you could pick just one thing"},{"time":58302,"text":"to lower the price of to reduce poverty,\nby far you would pick energy."},{"time":63702,"text":"Now, the price of energy\nhas come down over time."},{"time":67083,"text":"Really advanced civilization\nis based on advances in energy."},{"time":73778,"text":"The coal revolution fueled\nthe Industrial Revolution,"},{"time":77373,"text":"and, even in the 1900s,\nwe've seen a very rapid decline"},{"time":81458,"text":"in the price of electricity,"},{"time":83000,"text":"and that's why we have\nrefrigerators, air-conditioning;"},{"time":86406,"text":"we can make modern materials\nand do so many things."},{"time":90226,"text":"And so, we're in a wonderful situation\nwith electricity in the rich world."},{"time":97284,"text":"But as we make it cheaper --\nand let's say,"},{"time":100187,"text":"let's go for making it twice as cheap --"},{"time":104356,"text":"we need to meet a new constraint,"},{"time":106777,"text":"and that constraint has to do with CO2."}]},{"cues":[{"time":110743,"text":"CO2 is warming the planet,"},{"time":113836,"text":"and the equation on CO2\nis actually a very straightforward one."},{"time":119000,"text":"If you sum up the CO2 that gets emitted,"},{"time":123606,"text":"that leads to a temperature increase,"},{"time":126000,"text":"and that temperature increase\nleads to some very negative effects:"},{"time":130000,"text":"the effects on the weather;\nperhaps worse, the indirect effects,"},{"time":133937,"text":"in that the natural ecosystems\ncan't adjust to these rapid changes,"},{"time":138654,"text":"and so you get ecosystem collapses."}]},{"cues":[{"time":141400,"text":"Now, the exact amount of how you map\nfrom a certain increase of CO2"},{"time":146819,"text":"to what temperature will be,\nand where the positive feedbacks are --"},{"time":150133,"text":"there's some uncertainty there,\nbut not very much."},{"time":153266,"text":"And there's certainly uncertainty\nabout how bad those effects will be,"},{"time":156590,"text":"but they will be extremely bad."},{"time":159201,"text":"I asked the top scientists\non this several times:"},{"time":161527,"text":"Do we really have to get\ndown to near zero?"},{"time":164075,"text":"Can't we just cut it in half or a quarter?"},{"time":167132,"text":"And the answer is,\nuntil we get near to zero,"},{"time":171000,"text":"the temperature will continue to rise."},{"time":173458,"text":"And so that's a big challenge."},{"time":175252,"text":"It's very different than saying,"},{"time":177502,"text":"\"We're a twelve-foot-high truck\ntrying to get under a ten-foot bridge,"},{"time":180862,"text":"and we can just sort of squeeze under.\""},{"time":183609,"text":"This is something that has to get to zero."}]},{"cues":[{"time":187568,"text":"Now, we put out a lot\nof carbon dioxide every year --"},{"time":190861,"text":"over 26 billion tons."},{"time":193582,"text":"For each American, it's about 20 tons."},{"time":197178,"text":"For people in poor countries,\nit's less than one ton."},{"time":200000,"text":"It's an average of about five tons\nfor everyone on the planet."},{"time":204142,"text":"And somehow, we have to make changes\nthat will bring that down to zero."},{"time":209617,"text":"It's been constantly going up."},{"time":211785,"text":"It's only various economic changes\nthat have even flattened it at all,"},{"time":216414,"text":"so we have to go\nfrom rapidly rising to falling,"},{"time":219895,"text":"and falling all the way to zero."}]},{"cues":[{"time":222001,"text":"This equation has four factors,\na little bit of multiplication."},{"time":226000,"text":"So you've got a thing on the left,\nCO2, that you want to get to zero,"},{"time":229788,"text":"and that's going to be based\non the number of people,"},{"time":233202,"text":"the services each person\nis using on average,"},{"time":236616,"text":"the energy, on average, for each service,"},{"time":239509,"text":"and the CO2 being put out\nper unit of energy."},{"time":243732,"text":"So let's look at each one of these,"},{"time":245709,"text":"and see how we can get this down to zero."},{"time":249238,"text":"Probably, one of these numbers is going\nto have to get pretty near to zero."}]},{"cues":[{"time":252814,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":254020,"text":"That's back from high school algebra."},{"time":256018,"text":"But let's take a look."}]},{"cues":[{"time":257698,"text":"First, we've got population."},{"time":260194,"text":"The world today has 6.8 billion people."},{"time":263000,"text":"That's headed up to about nine billion."},{"time":265227,"text":"Now, if we do a really great job\non new vaccines,"},{"time":269312,"text":"health care, reproductive health services,"},{"time":271793,"text":"we could lower that by,\nperhaps, 10 or 15 percent."},{"time":274918,"text":"But there, we see\nan increase of about 1.3."}]},{"cues":[{"time":279425,"text":"The second factor is the services we use."},{"time":282455,"text":"This encompasses everything:"},{"time":284244,"text":"the food we eat, clothing, TV, heating."},{"time":288777,"text":"These are very good things."},{"time":290929,"text":"Getting rid of poverty means\nproviding these services"},{"time":294660,"text":"to almost everyone on the planet."},{"time":296689,"text":"And it's a great thing\nfor this number to go up."},{"time":300000,"text":"In the rich world, perhaps\nthe top one billion,"},{"time":302263,"text":"we probably could cut back and use less,"},{"time":304672,"text":"but every year, this number,\non average, is going to go up,"},{"time":308812,"text":"and so, overall,\nthat will more than double"},{"time":312000,"text":"the services delivered per person."},{"time":315138,"text":"Here we have a very basic service:"},{"time":317265,"text":"Do you have lighting in your house\nto be able to read your homework?"},{"time":320701,"text":"And, in fact, these kids don't,"},{"time":322244,"text":"so they're going out and reading\ntheir schoolwork"},{"time":324586,"text":"under the street lamps."}]},{"cues":[{"time":327278,"text":"Now, efficiency, \"E,\"\nthe energy for each service --"},{"time":331000,"text":"here, finally we have some good news."},{"time":333001,"text":"We have something that's not going up."},{"time":334887,"text":"Through various inventions\nand new ways of doing lighting,"},{"time":338000,"text":"through different types of cars,\ndifferent ways of building buildings --"},{"time":343455,"text":"there are a lot of services"},{"time":345114,"text":"where you can bring the energy\nfor that service down"},{"time":348478,"text":"quite substantially."},{"time":350000,"text":"Some individual services\neven bring it down by 90 percent."},{"time":353519,"text":"There are other services,\nlike how we make fertilizer,"},{"time":356889,"text":"or how we do air transport,"},{"time":358555,"text":"where the rooms for improvement\nare far, far less."},{"time":361896,"text":"And so overall, if we're optimistic,\nwe may get a reduction"},{"time":366218,"text":"of a factor of three to even,\nperhaps, a factor of six."},{"time":371608,"text":"But for these first three factors now,"},{"time":374000,"text":"we've gone from 26 billion\nto, at best, maybe 13 billion tons,"},{"time":379084,"text":"and that just won't cut it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":380999,"text":"So let's look at this fourth factor --\nthis is going to be a key one --"},{"time":384821,"text":"and this is the amount of CO2\nput out per each unit of energy."},{"time":391174,"text":"So the question is:\nCan you actually get that to zero?"},{"time":394723,"text":"If you burn coal, no."},{"time":397653,"text":"If you burn natural gas, no."},{"time":399152,"text":"Almost every way\nwe make electricity today,"},{"time":402279,"text":"except for the emerging renewables\nand nuclear, puts out CO2."},{"time":408291,"text":"And so, what we're going to have\nto do at a global scale,"},{"time":411568,"text":"is create a new system."},{"time":413873,"text":"So we need energy miracles."}]},{"cues":[{"time":416526,"text":"Now, when I use the term \"miracle,\"\nI don't mean something that's impossible."},{"time":420843,"text":"The microprocessor is a miracle."},{"time":423287,"text":"The personal computer is a miracle."},{"time":425296,"text":"The Internet and its services\nare a miracle."},{"time":427787,"text":"So the people here have participated\nin the creation of many miracles."},{"time":432857,"text":"Usually, we don't have a deadline"},{"time":434858,"text":"where you have to get the miracle\nby a certain date."},{"time":437360,"text":"Usually, you just kind of stand by,\nand some come along, some don't."},{"time":441365,"text":"This is a case where we actually\nhave to drive at full speed"},{"time":445488,"text":"and get a miracle\nin a pretty tight timeline."}]},{"cues":[{"time":450489,"text":"Now, I thought, \"How could\nI really capture this?"},{"time":453458,"text":"Is there some kind\nof natural illustration,"},{"time":455705,"text":"some demonstration that would grab\npeople's imagination here?\""},{"time":460242,"text":"I thought back to a year ago\nwhen I brought mosquitoes,"},{"time":464000,"text":"and somehow people enjoyed that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":466654,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":468285,"text":"It really got them involved\nin the idea of, you know,"},{"time":472355,"text":"there are people who live with mosquitoes."},{"time":474431,"text":"With energy, all I could\ncome up with is this."},{"time":478841,"text":"I decided that releasing fireflies"},{"time":481999,"text":"would be my contribution\nto the environment here this year."},{"time":486116,"text":"So here we have some natural fireflies."},{"time":489000,"text":"I'm told they don't bite; in fact,\nthey might not even leave that jar."}]},{"cues":[{"time":492633,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":495833,"text":"Now, there's all sorts of gimmicky\nsolutions like that one,"},{"time":499995,"text":"but they don't really add up to much."},{"time":501920,"text":"We need solutions, either one or several,"},{"time":505967,"text":"that have unbelievable scale\nand unbelievable reliability."},{"time":512008,"text":"And although there's many directions\nthat people are seeking,"},{"time":515500,"text":"I really only see five\nthat can achieve the big numbers."},{"time":519601,"text":"I've left out tide,\ngeothermal, fusion, biofuels."},{"time":523912,"text":"Those may make some contribution,"},{"time":525913,"text":"and if they can do better\nthan I expect, so much the better."},{"time":528786,"text":"But my key point here\nis that we're going to have to work on"},{"time":532732,"text":"each of these five,"},{"time":534482,"text":"and we can't give up any of them\nbecause they look daunting,"},{"time":538303,"text":"because they all have\nsignificant challenges."}]},{"cues":[{"time":541801,"text":"Let's look first at burning fossil fuels,"},{"time":544445,"text":"either burning coal\nor burning natural gas."},{"time":547761,"text":"What you need to do there seems\nlike it might be simple, but it's not."},{"time":551871,"text":"And that's to take all the CO2,"},{"time":554328,"text":"after you've burned it,\ngoing out the flue,"},{"time":557000,"text":"pressurize it, create a liquid,\nput it somewhere,"},{"time":560169,"text":"and hope it stays there."},{"time":562192,"text":"Now, we have some pilot things"},{"time":563838,"text":"that do this at the 60 to 80\npercent level."},{"time":566201,"text":"But getting up to that full percentage --\nthat will be very tricky."},{"time":570624,"text":"And agreeing on where these CO2\nquantities should be put will be hard,"},{"time":576220,"text":"but the toughest one here\nis this long-term issue:"},{"time":578906,"text":"Who's going to be sure?"},{"time":580470,"text":"Who's going to guarantee"},{"time":582092,"text":"something that is literally\nbillions of times larger"},{"time":585185,"text":"than any type of waste you think of\nin terms of nuclear or other things?"},{"time":589355,"text":"This is a lot of volume."},{"time":592434,"text":"So that's a tough one."}]},{"cues":[{"time":594267,"text":"Next would be nuclear."},{"time":596000,"text":"It also has three big problems:"},{"time":599000,"text":"cost, particularly in highly\nregulated countries, is high;"},{"time":603000,"text":"the issue of safety, really feeling good\nabout nothing could go wrong,"},{"time":607678,"text":"that, even though you have\nthese human operators,"},{"time":610706,"text":"the fuel doesn't get used for weapons."},{"time":613456,"text":"And then what do you do with the waste?"},{"time":615435,"text":"Although it's not very large,\nthere are a lot of concerns about that."},{"time":618863,"text":"People need to feel good about it."},{"time":620552,"text":"So three very tough problems\nthat might be solvable,"},{"time":625000,"text":"and so, should be worked on."}]},{"cues":[{"time":627189,"text":"The last three of the five,\nI've grouped together."},{"time":629904,"text":"These are what people often refer to\nas the renewable sources."},{"time":633841,"text":"And they actually -- although it's great\nthey don't require fuel --"},{"time":637888,"text":"they have some disadvantages."},{"time":640317,"text":"One is that the density of energy\ngathered in these technologies"},{"time":646183,"text":"is dramatically less than a power plant."},{"time":648270,"text":"This is energy farming,"},{"time":649976,"text":"so you're talking about many square miles,\nthousands of times more area"},{"time":654121,"text":"than you think of\nas a normal energy plant."},{"time":657498,"text":"Also, these are intermittent sources."},{"time":660110,"text":"The sun doesn't shine all day,\nit doesn't shine every day,"},{"time":663549,"text":"and likewise, the wind\ndoesn't blow all the time."},{"time":666000,"text":"And so, if you depend on these sources,"},{"time":668413,"text":"you have to have some way\nof getting the energy"},{"time":670787,"text":"during those time periods\nthat it's not available."},{"time":674158,"text":"So we've got big cost challenges here."},{"time":677238,"text":"We have transmission challenges;"},{"time":679160,"text":"for example, say this energy source\nis outside your country,"},{"time":682748,"text":"you not only need the technology,"},{"time":684865,"text":"but you have to deal with the risk\nof the energy coming from elsewhere."}]},{"cues":[{"time":689262,"text":"And, finally, this storage problem."},{"time":691800,"text":"To dimensionalize this,"},{"time":693325,"text":"I went through and looked\nat all the types of batteries made --"},{"time":696902,"text":"for cars, for computers, for phones,\nfor flashlights, for everything --"},{"time":701438,"text":"and compared that to the amount\nof electrical energy the world uses."},{"time":706384,"text":"What I found is that all\nthe batteries we make now"},{"time":710001,"text":"could store less than 10 minutes\nof all the energy."},{"time":714000,"text":"And so, in fact, we need\na big breakthrough here,"},{"time":717392,"text":"something that's going to be\na factor of 100 better"},{"time":721284,"text":"than the approaches we have now."},{"time":723141,"text":"It's not impossible,\nbut it's not a very easy thing."},{"time":727334,"text":"Now, this shows up when you try\nto get the intermittent source"},{"time":731000,"text":"to be above, say, 20 to 30 percent\nof what you're using."},{"time":735176,"text":"If you're counting on it for 100 percent,"},{"time":737794,"text":"you need an incredible miracle battery."}]},{"cues":[{"time":743000,"text":"Now, how are we going to go forward\non this -- what's the right approach?"},{"time":746641,"text":"Is it a Manhattan Project?\nWhat's the thing that can get us there?"},{"time":750244,"text":"Well, we need lots of companies\nworking on this -- hundreds."},{"time":755079,"text":"In each of these five paths,\nwe need at least a hundred people."},{"time":758682,"text":"A lot of them, you'll look at\nand say, \"They're crazy.\""},{"time":761416,"text":"That's good."},{"time":762621,"text":"And, I think, here in the TED group,"},{"time":765575,"text":"we have many people\nwho are already pursuing this."},{"time":769556,"text":"Bill Gross has several companies,\nincluding one called eSolar"},{"time":773000,"text":"that has some great\nsolar thermal technologies."},{"time":775806,"text":"Vinod Khosla is investing\nin dozens of companies"},{"time":779280,"text":"that are doing great things\nand have interesting possibilities,"},{"time":783231,"text":"and I'm trying to help back that."},{"time":785404,"text":"Nathan Myhrvold and I\nactually are backing a company"},{"time":789000,"text":"that, perhaps surprisingly,\nis actually taking the nuclear approach."},{"time":792796,"text":"There are some innovations\nin nuclear: modular, liquid."},{"time":797398,"text":"Innovation really stopped\nin this industry quite some ago,"},{"time":801195,"text":"so the idea that there's some\ngood ideas laying around"},{"time":804314,"text":"is not all that surprising."}]},{"cues":[{"time":806529,"text":"The idea of TerraPower is that,\ninstead of burning a part of uranium --"},{"time":812343,"text":"the one percent, which is the U235 --"},{"time":815486,"text":"we decided, \"Let's burn\nthe 99 percent, the U238.\""},{"time":819738,"text":"It is kind of a crazy idea."},{"time":822115,"text":"In fact, people had talked\nabout it for a long time,"},{"time":825282,"text":"but they could never simulate properly\nwhether it would work or not,"},{"time":829467,"text":"and so it's through the advent\nof modern supercomputers"},{"time":832356,"text":"that now you can simulate\nand see that, yes,"},{"time":834511,"text":"with the right materials approach,\nthis looks like it would work."}]},{"cues":[{"time":840193,"text":"And because you're burning\nthat 99 percent,"},{"time":843000,"text":"you have greatly improved cost profile."},{"time":847407,"text":"You actually burn up the waste,\nand you can actually use as fuel"},{"time":851641,"text":"all the leftover waste\nfrom today's reactors."},{"time":854690,"text":"So instead of worrying about them,\nyou just take that, it's a great thing."},{"time":858828,"text":"It breeds this uranium as it goes along,\nso it's kind of like a candle."},{"time":863347,"text":"You see it's a log there, often\nreferred to as a traveling wave reactor."},{"time":867500,"text":"In terms of fuel,\nthis really solves the problem."},{"time":871443,"text":"I've got a picture here\nof a place in Kentucky."},{"time":874368,"text":"This is the leftover, the 99 percent,"},{"time":876592,"text":"where they've taken out\nthe part they burn now,"},{"time":878846,"text":"so it's called depleted uranium."},{"time":880440,"text":"That would power the US\nfor hundreds of years."},{"time":883311,"text":"And simply by filtering seawater\nin an inexpensive process,"},{"time":886870,"text":"you'd have enough fuel for the entire\nlifetime of the rest of the planet."}]},{"cues":[{"time":891054,"text":"So, you know, it's got lots\nof challenges ahead,"},{"time":895139,"text":"but it is an example of the many\nhundreds and hundreds of ideas"},{"time":900558,"text":"that we need to move forward."},{"time":903407,"text":"So let's think: How should\nwe measure ourselves?"},{"time":906129,"text":"What should our report card look like?"},{"time":909356,"text":"Well, let's go out to where\nwe really need to get,"},{"time":911904,"text":"and then look at the intermediate."},{"time":914071,"text":"For 2050, you've heard many people\ntalk about this 80 percent reduction."},{"time":919842,"text":"That really is very important,\nthat we get there."},{"time":922918,"text":"And that 20 percent will be used up\nby things going on in poor countries --"},{"time":927363,"text":"still some agriculture; hopefully,\nwe will have cleaned up forestry, cement."},{"time":932781,"text":"So, to get to that 80 percent,"},{"time":935794,"text":"the developed countries,\nincluding countries like China,"},{"time":940323,"text":"will have had to switch\ntheir electricity generation altogether."},{"time":945125,"text":"The other grade is: Are we deploying\nthis zero-emission technology,"},{"time":951000,"text":"have we deployed it\nin all the developed countries"},{"time":953421,"text":"and are in the process\nof getting it elsewhere?"},{"time":956232,"text":"That's super important."},{"time":958000,"text":"That's a key element\nof making that report card."}]},{"cues":[{"time":962000,"text":"Backing up from there, what should\nthe 2020 report card look like?"},{"time":966755,"text":"Well, again, it should have\nthe two elements."},{"time":969097,"text":"We should go through these efficiency\nmeasures to start getting reductions:"},{"time":973260,"text":"The less we emit,\nthe less that sum will be of CO2,"},{"time":976548,"text":"and therefore, the less the temperature."},{"time":978644,"text":"But in some ways, the grade we get there,"},{"time":981597,"text":"doing things that don't get us\nall the way to the big reductions,"},{"time":985865,"text":"is only equally, or maybe even slightly\nless, important than the other,"},{"time":989733,"text":"which is the piece of innovation\non these breakthroughs."}]},{"cues":[{"time":993513,"text":"These breakthroughs,\nwe need to move those at full speed,"},{"time":996775,"text":"and we can measure that\nin terms of companies,"},{"time":999224,"text":"pilot projects, regulatory things\nthat have been changed."},{"time":1002598,"text":"There's a lot of great books\nthat have been written about this."},{"time":1005596,"text":"The Al Gore book, \"Our Choice,\""},{"time":1008000,"text":"and the David MacKay book,\n\"Sustainable Energy Without the Hot Air.\""},{"time":1011604,"text":"They really go through it\nand create a framework"},{"time":1014804,"text":"that this can be discussed broadly,"},{"time":1016661,"text":"because we need broad backing for this."},{"time":1018986,"text":"There's a lot that has to come together."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1021237,"text":"So this is a wish."},{"time":1022743,"text":"It's a very concrete wish\nthat we invent this technology."},{"time":1027372,"text":"If you gave me only one wish\nfor the next 50 years --"},{"time":1030485,"text":"I could pick who's president,"},{"time":1032486,"text":"I could pick a vaccine,\nwhich is something I love,"},{"time":1035272,"text":"or I could pick that this thing"},{"time":1037353,"text":"that's half the cost with no CO2\ngets invented --"},{"time":1040838,"text":"this is the wish I would pick."},{"time":1042769,"text":"This is the one with the greatest impact."},{"time":1044878,"text":"If we don't get this wish,"},{"time":1046547,"text":"the division between the people\nwho think short term and long term"},{"time":1050009,"text":"will be terrible,"},{"time":1051191,"text":"between the US and China,\nbetween poor countries and rich,"},{"time":1054159,"text":"and most of all,"},{"time":1055377,"text":"the lives of those two billion\nwill be far worse."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1059158,"text":"So what do we have to do?"},{"time":1061000,"text":"What am I appealing to you\nto step forward and drive?"},{"time":1066189,"text":"We need to go for more research funding."},{"time":1069190,"text":"When countries get together\nin places like Copenhagen,"},{"time":1071839,"text":"they shouldn't just discuss the CO2."},{"time":1074282,"text":"They should discuss\nthis innovation agenda."},{"time":1076673,"text":"You'd be stunned at the ridiculously\nlow levels of spending"},{"time":1081000,"text":"on these innovative approaches."},{"time":1083183,"text":"We do need the market incentives --\nCO2 tax, cap and trade --"},{"time":1087000,"text":"something that gets\nthat price signal out there."},{"time":1089881,"text":"We need to get the message out."},{"time":1091503,"text":"We need to have this dialogue\nbe a more rational,"},{"time":1093931,"text":"more understandable dialogue,"},{"time":1095545,"text":"including the steps\nthat the government takes."},{"time":1098100,"text":"This is an important wish,\nbut it is one I think we can achieve."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1102416,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1103593,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":1112975,"text":"(Applause ends)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1115000,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1117303,"text":"Chris Anderson: Thank you. Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1119172,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1124257,"text":"CA: Thank you."},{"time":1125779,"text":"So to understand more about TerraPower."},{"time":1130399,"text":"I mean, first of all, can you give a sense\nof what scale of investment this is?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1134898,"text":"Bill Gates: To actually do the software,\nbuy the supercomputer,"},{"time":1139256,"text":"hire all the great scientists,\nwhich we've done,"},{"time":1141609,"text":"that's only tens of millions."},{"time":1143890,"text":"And even once we test our materials out\nin a Russian reactor"},{"time":1147862,"text":"to make sure our materials work properly,"},{"time":1151061,"text":"then you'll only be up\nin the hundreds of millions."},{"time":1153602,"text":"The tough thing\nis building the pilot reactor --"},{"time":1155984,"text":"finding the several billion,\nfinding the regulator, the location"},{"time":1160812,"text":"that will actually build\nthe first one of these."},{"time":1163095,"text":"Once you get the first one built,\nif it works as advertised,"},{"time":1167281,"text":"then it's just clear as day,"},{"time":1168655,"text":"because the economics,\nthe energy density, are so different"},{"time":1171875,"text":"than nuclear as we know it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1173313,"text":"CA: So to understand it right,"},{"time":1174799,"text":"this involves building\ndeep into the ground,"},{"time":1177105,"text":"almost like a vertical column\nof nuclear fuel, of this spent uranium,"},{"time":1182689,"text":"and then the process starts\nat the top and kind of works down?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1185853,"text":"BG: That's right."},{"time":1187054,"text":"Today, you're always\nrefueling the reactor,"},{"time":1189137,"text":"so you have lots of people and lots\nof controls that can go wrong,"},{"time":1192353,"text":"where you're opening it up\nand moving things in and out --"},{"time":1195116,"text":"that's not good."},{"time":1197297,"text":"So if you have very --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1198494,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1199607,"text":"very cheap fuel\nthat you can put 60 years in --"},{"time":1202378,"text":"just think of it as a log --"},{"time":1203956,"text":"put it down and not have\nthose same complexities."},{"time":1207518,"text":"And it just sits there and burns\nfor the 60 years, and then it's done."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1212447,"text":"CA: It's a nuclear power plant\nthat is its own waste disposal solution."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1216409,"text":"BG: Yeah; what happens with the waste,"},{"time":1218327,"text":"you can let it sit there -- there's a lot\nless waste under this approach --"},{"time":1223731,"text":"then you can actually take that"},{"time":1225391,"text":"and put it into another one and burn that."},{"time":1228000,"text":"And we start out, actually,\nby taking the waste that exists today"},{"time":1232230,"text":"that's sitting in these cooling pools\nor dry-casking by reactors --"},{"time":1236486,"text":"that's our fuel to begin with."},{"time":1238662,"text":"So the thing that's been a problem\nfrom those reactors"},{"time":1241293,"text":"is actually what gets fed into ours,"},{"time":1243244,"text":"and you're reducing the volume\nof the waste quite dramatically"},{"time":1246255,"text":"as you're going through this process."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1248256,"text":"CA: You're talking\nto different people around the world"},{"time":1250855,"text":"about the possibilities."},{"time":1252168,"text":"Where is there most interest\nin actually doing something with this?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1255600,"text":"BG: Well, we haven't picked\na particular place,"},{"time":1259779,"text":"and there's all these interesting\ndisclosure rules"},{"time":1263263,"text":"about anything that's called \"nuclear.\""},{"time":1265763,"text":"So we've got a lot of interest."},{"time":1268716,"text":"People from the company\nhave been in Russia, India, China."},{"time":1271815,"text":"I've been back seeing\nthe secretary of energy here,"},{"time":1274453,"text":"talking about how this fits\ninto the energy agenda."},{"time":1277809,"text":"So I'm optimistic."},{"time":1279409,"text":"The French and Japanese\nhave done some work."},{"time":1281610,"text":"This is a variant on something\nthat has been done."},{"time":1285294,"text":"It's an important advance,\nbut it's like a fast reactor,"},{"time":1289000,"text":"and a lot of countries have built them,"},{"time":1291000,"text":"so anybody who's done\na fast reactor is a candidate"},{"time":1293598,"text":"to be where the first one gets built."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1296000,"text":"CA: So, in your mind,"},{"time":1299466,"text":"timescale and likelihood of actually\ntaking something like this live?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1304248,"text":"BG: Well, we need -- for one of these\nhigh-scale, electro-generation things"},{"time":1310359,"text":"that's very cheap,"},{"time":1311541,"text":"we have 20 years to invent\nand then 20 years to deploy."},{"time":1315243,"text":"That's sort of the deadline"},{"time":1317023,"text":"that the environmental models\nhave shown us that we have to meet."},{"time":1322305,"text":"And TerraPower -- if things go well,\nwhich is wishing for a lot --"},{"time":1327741,"text":"could easily meet that."},{"time":1329408,"text":"And there are, fortunately\nnow, dozens of companies --"},{"time":1332704,"text":"we need it to be hundreds --"},{"time":1334079,"text":"who, likewise, if their science goes well,"},{"time":1336320,"text":"if the funding for their pilot\nplants goes well,"},{"time":1339239,"text":"that they can compete for this."},{"time":1341289,"text":"And it's best if multiple succeed,"},{"time":1343287,"text":"because then you could use\na mix of these things."},{"time":1346000,"text":"We certainly need one to succeed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1348105,"text":"CA: In terms of big-scale\npossible game changers,"},{"time":1351088,"text":"is this the biggest\nthat you're aware of out there?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1353846,"text":"BG: An energy breakthrough\nis the most important thing."},{"time":1358219,"text":"It would have been, even\nwithout the environmental constraint,"},{"time":1361226,"text":"but the environmental constraint\njust makes it so much greater."},{"time":1365113,"text":"In the nuclear space,\nthere are other innovators."},{"time":1368461,"text":"You know, we don't know their work\nas well as we know this one,"},{"time":1371475,"text":"but the modular people,\nthat's a different approach."},{"time":1374756,"text":"There's a liquid-type reactor,\nwhich seems a little hard,"},{"time":1378385,"text":"but maybe they say that about us."},{"time":1380645,"text":"And so, there are different ones,"},{"time":1383000,"text":"but the beauty of this\nis a molecule of uranium"},{"time":1386000,"text":"has a million times as much energy\nas a molecule of, say, coal."},{"time":1390702,"text":"And so, if you can\ndeal with the negatives,"},{"time":1393742,"text":"which are essentially the radiation,\nthe footprint and cost,"},{"time":1397618,"text":"the potential, in terms of effect\non land and various things,"},{"time":1401633,"text":"is almost in a class of its own."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1406039,"text":"CA: If this doesn't work, then what?"},{"time":1409702,"text":"Do we have to start taking\nemergency measures"},{"time":1413000,"text":"to try and keep the temperature\nof the earth stable?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1416122,"text":"BG: If you get into that situation,"},{"time":1418000,"text":"it's like if you've been overeating,\nand you're about to have a heart attack."},{"time":1423000,"text":"Then where do you go?"},{"time":1425549,"text":"You may need heart surgery or something."},{"time":1427506,"text":"There is a line of research\non what's called geoengineering,"},{"time":1431400,"text":"which are various techniques\nthat would delay the heating"},{"time":1434401,"text":"to buy us 20 or 30 years\nto get our act together."},{"time":1437711,"text":"Now, that's just an insurance policy;\nyou hope you don't need to do that."},{"time":1441343,"text":"Some people say you shouldn't even\nwork on the insurance policy"},{"time":1444409,"text":"because it might make you lazy,"},{"time":1445954,"text":"that you'll keep eating because you know\nheart surgery will be there to save you."},{"time":1449844,"text":"I'm not sure that's wise,\ngiven the importance of the problem,"},{"time":1452985,"text":"but there's now\nthe geoengineering discussion"},{"time":1456110,"text":"about: Should that be in the back\npocket in case things happen faster,"},{"time":1460341,"text":"or this innovation goes\na lot slower than we expect?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1465549,"text":"CA: Climate skeptics:"},{"time":1467374,"text":"If you had a sentence or two\nto say to them,"},{"time":1470904,"text":"how might you persuade them\nthat they're wrong?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1475645,"text":"BG: Well, unfortunately,\nthe skeptics come in different camps."},{"time":1478720,"text":"The ones who make scientific\narguments are very few."},{"time":1483185,"text":"Are they saying there's negative\nfeedback effects"},{"time":1486198,"text":"that have to do with clouds\nthat offset things?"},{"time":1488424,"text":"There are very, very few things\nthat they can even say"},{"time":1491756,"text":"there's a chance\nin a million of those things."},{"time":1494427,"text":"The main problem we have here --\nit's kind of like with AIDS:"},{"time":1497655,"text":"you make the mistake now,\nand you pay for it a lot later."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1501482,"text":"And so, when you have\nall sorts of urgent problems,"},{"time":1504761,"text":"the idea of taking pain now\nthat has to do with a gain later,"},{"time":1508846,"text":"and a somewhat uncertain pain thing."},{"time":1511156,"text":"In fact, the IPCC report --\nthat's not necessarily the worst case,"},{"time":1517268,"text":"and there are people in the rich world\nwho look at IPCC and say,"},{"time":1521367,"text":"\"OK, that isn't that big of a deal.\""},{"time":1523175,"text":"The fact is it's that uncertain part\nthat should move us towards this."},{"time":1527348,"text":"But my dream here is that,"},{"time":1529004,"text":"if you can make it economic,\nand meet the CO2 constraints,"},{"time":1532688,"text":"then the skeptics say,"},{"time":1533871,"text":"\"OK, I don't care\nthat it doesn't put out CO2,"},{"time":1536175,"text":"I kind of wish it did put out CO2."},{"time":1537879,"text":"But I guess I'll accept it,"},{"time":1539259,"text":"because it's cheaper\nthan what's come before.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":1542000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1546855,"text":"CA: So that would be your response\nto the Bjørn Lomborg argument,"},{"time":1550059,"text":"basically if you spend all this energy\ntrying to solve the CO2 problem,"},{"time":1554539,"text":"it's going to take away\nall your other goals"},{"time":1556657,"text":"of trying to rid the world\nof poverty and malaria and so forth,"},{"time":1559674,"text":"it's a stupid waste\nof the Earth's resources"},{"time":1561931,"text":"to put money towards that"},{"time":1563228,"text":"when there are better things we can do."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1565170,"text":"BG: Well, the actual\nspending on the R&amp;D piece --"},{"time":1568585,"text":"say the US should spend 10 billion a year\nmore than it is right now --"},{"time":1572105,"text":"it's not that dramatic."},{"time":1574000,"text":"It shouldn't take away from other things."},{"time":1576000,"text":"The thing you get into big money on,\nand reasonable people can disagree,"},{"time":1579444,"text":"is when you have something\nthat's non-economic"},{"time":1581634,"text":"and you're trying to fund that --"},{"time":1583277,"text":"that, to me, mostly is a waste."},{"time":1585229,"text":"Unless you're very close,"},{"time":1586800,"text":"and you're just funding the learning curve\nand it's going to get very cheap,"},{"time":1590468,"text":"I believe we should try more things"},{"time":1593290,"text":"that have a potential\nto be far less expensive."},{"time":1596000,"text":"If the trade-off you get into is,\n\"Let's make energy super expensive,\""},{"time":1601216,"text":"then the rich can afford that."},{"time":1603262,"text":"I mean, all of us here could pay\nfive times as much for our energy"},{"time":1606415,"text":"and not change our lifestyle."},{"time":1607830,"text":"The disaster is for that two billion."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1610118,"text":"And even Lomborg has changed."},{"time":1612449,"text":"His shtick now is, \"Why isn't the R&amp;D\ngetting more discussed?\""},{"time":1617000,"text":"He's still, because of his earlier stuff,"},{"time":1619537,"text":"still associated with the skeptic camp,"},{"time":1621461,"text":"but he's realized\nthat's a pretty lonely camp,"},{"time":1624258,"text":"and so, he's making the R&amp;D point."},{"time":1627540,"text":"And so there is a thread of something\nthat I think is appropriate."},{"time":1632000,"text":"The R&amp;D piece --\nit's crazy how little it's funded."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1635556,"text":"CA: Well, Bill, I suspect I speak\non behalf of most people here"},{"time":1638867,"text":"to say I really hope your wish comes true."},{"time":1640959,"text":"Thank you so much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1642155,"text":"BG: Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1643330,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}